<task id="AIPU2-085" project="Spaarke AI Platform Unification R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Build RedlineViewerWidget for Document Comparison</title>
    <phase>4D</phase>
    <tags>frontend, widgets, documents</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>AIPU2-071, AIPU2-042</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    Legal workflows frequently require side-by-side document comparison with tracked changes.
    AIPU2-042 implemented the server-side document comparison BFF endpoint that returns a
    structured diff (additions, deletions, modifications by section). RedlineViewerWidget
    consumes this diff and renders it as a side-by-side view in the Workspace pane: left side
    shows the original document, right side shows the modified version, with change type
    highlights (additions in green, deletions in red, modifications in yellow using Fluent v9
    semantic color tokens). Section-level navigation allows jumping between changed sections.
    Widget must implement serializeState/restoreState via data-refreshed restore (re-call BFF
    with the comparison identifiers).
  </prompt>
  <role>Frontend developer with React 19, Fluent v9, and document diff rendering experience.</role>
  <goal>
    Two document versions display side-by-side with changes highlighted using Fluent v9 semantic
    color tokens. Section navigation works. Serialize/restore calls BFF for fresh diff data.
    Widget registered in WorkspaceWidgetRegistry.
  </goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Read ADR-021 to understand the Fluent v9 design token requirements — no hard-coded colors, dark mode required, use semantic tokens (colorPaletteGreenBackground2, colorPaletteRedBackground2, colorPaletteYellowBackground2 or equivalent).</step>
    <step>Create src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/RedlineViewerWidget.tsx implementing WorkspaceWidget&lt;RedlineViewerData, RedlineViewerActions&gt;.</step>
    <step>Define RedlineViewerData type: { documentAId: string; documentBId: string; comparisonId: string; sections: DiffSection[] } where DiffSection carries the change type and text content for both sides.</step>
    <step>Render a two-column layout (Fluent v9 Grid or CSS grid): left column = original text, right column = modified text, synchronized scroll.</step>
    <step>Apply Fluent v9 semantic color tokens to highlight change regions: additions (colorPaletteGreenBackground2 or equivalent), deletions (colorPaletteRedBackground2), modifications (colorPaletteYellowBackground2). Verify tokens work in both light and dark themes.</step>
    <step>Implement section-level navigation: a navigation panel lists changed section titles; clicking a section scrolls both columns to that section simultaneously.</step>
    <step>Implement serializeState(): return { widgetType: 'redline-viewer', version: 1, data: { documentAId, documentBId, comparisonId }, timestamp }.</step>
    <step>Implement restoreState(state): call BFF comparison endpoint with documentAId, documentBId, comparisonId to re-fetch fresh diff data; update widget display.</step>
    <step>Register RedlineViewerWidget in WorkspaceWidgetRegistry with displayName: 'Document Comparison', category: 'document'.</step>
    <step>Write unit tests: change highlights use correct Fluent tokens for each change type; section navigation scrolls to the correct section; serializeState returns only identifiers.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Side-by-side diff view renders additions (green), deletions (red), modifications (yellow) using Fluent v9 semantic color tokens — no hard-coded colors.</criterion>
    <criterion>Dark mode: all highlight colors remain distinguishable using Fluent v9 dark theme tokens.</criterion>
    <criterion>Section-level navigation lists all changed sections and scrolls both columns correctly.</criterion>
    <criterion>serializeState returns only document identifiers (not full diff data).</criterion>
    <criterion>restoreState calls BFF comparison endpoint and refreshes the widget with the response.</criterion>
    <criterion>Widget registered in WorkspaceWidgetRegistry and renders in WorkspacePane tabs.</criterion>
    <criterion>Unit tests for highlight tokens, navigation, and serialize pass.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
